German States to Propose Tax Law Simplification, Rheinische Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-10-12T19:52:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/german-states-to-propose-tax-law-simplification-rheinische-says.html
Four German states want to simplify
the country’s tax law,  Rheinische Post  reported, citing an
internal paper.  The states of Hesse, Bremen, Schleswig-Holstein and
Rhineland-Palatinate will present the plan on Oct. 14 and aim to
bring the proposal to  Germany ’s upper house of parliament, or
Bundesrat, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  